{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1071"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Bakery Products Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1071"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :food/bakery-products
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :food-safety :fair-labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :bakery-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "BakeryOpsAdvisor ⊣ Bakery Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, bakeryops.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (bakeryops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore
 backed by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A plant-operations
 COORDINATION actor for bakery-products manufacturing (bread/pastry/
 cake) -- not direct mixing/baking-line control authority and not
 food-safety certification authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-food-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten independent HARD Governor checks (spec-basis,
 evidence-completeness, baking-temp/time, moisture, sanitation-score,
 scale-calibration, weight-variance, allergen-label, unresolved
 food-safety flag, double-commit guards) elaborate this blueprint's
 Governor (`bakeryops.governor`/`bakeryops.registry`). Batch logging
 and shipment coordination -- this actor's two real actuation events --
 and food-safety-concern flagging ALWAYS escalate to a human plant
 operator via the compiled graph's `:request-approval` node
 (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based resume); `:schedule-maintenance`
 is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only when the Governor is
 clean. Every commit/hold/approval-rejected decision lands in the
 append-only ledger, demo runnable end-to-end against both Store
 backends (`clojure -M:dev:run`)."}
